      • onOperate

        CommandFlow onOperate​(Module module,
                      CommandFlow left,
                      CommandFlow center,
                      CommandFlow right)
               throws CommandException
        This method is called when the operator operates on a CommandFlow.
        Parameters:
        module - The Module that is being operated on.
        left - The left CommandFlow that is being operated on.
        center - The center CommandFlow that is being operated on.
        right - The right CommandFlow that is being operated on.
        Returns:
        The CommandFlow that is the result of the operation.
        Throws:
        CommandException - If an error occurs during the operation.
